org.datavec.dataframe.columns

Interface Column<E extends Column>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BooleanColumnUtils, BooleanMapUtils, CategoryColumnUtils, CategoryFilters, CategoryReduceUtils, DateColumnUtils, DateMapUtils, DateTImeColumnUtils, DateTimeMapUtils, DoubleColumnUtils, FloatColumnUtils, IntColumnUtils, IntMapUtils, LongColumnUtils, LongMapUtils, NumericColumn, ShortColumnUtils, ShortMapUtils, StringMapUtils, TimeColumnUtils, TimeMapUtils
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractColumn, BooleanColumn, CategoryColumn, DateColumn, DateTimeColumn, DoubleColumn, FloatColumn, IntColumn, LongColumn, ShortColumn, TimeColumn

    public interface Column<E extends Column>
    The general interface for columns.

    Columns can either exist on their own or be a part of a table. All the data in a single column is of a particular type.

        E difference()
        Returns a new column of the same type as the receiver, such that the values in the new column contain the difference between each cell in the original and it's predecessor. The Missing Value Indicator is used for the first cell in the new column. (e.g. IntColumn.MISSING_VALUE)
